<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="366" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" box="[151,746,1820,1845]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,244,1820,1845]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[323,409,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
(n=5); female: 
<quantity box="[583,669,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(n=4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" box="[199,1436,1856,1881]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1856,1881]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Morphology.</emphasis>
Crown longer than distance between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[837,903,1856,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,925,947]" captionTargetBox="[238,1350,209,894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,916]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. male: A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C. face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A). Male anteclypeus tapered distally (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1402,1856,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,925,947]" captionTargetBox="[238,1350,209,894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,916]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. male: A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C. face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1892,1917]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate long, lateral margin distinctly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1092,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
C). Style with articulating arm short; preapical lobe rectangular; apophysis thick fingerlike, apex subtruncate (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1120,1928,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
D). Connective shorter than aedeagus. Aedeagus slender, tapered from base to apex, curved dorsad with pair of slender apical appendages directed distad (
<figureCitation box="[330,395,2000,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" targetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1470,1553]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1470,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[285,433,1470,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[285,433,1470,1492]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Cortona silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[441,500,1471,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[441,500,1471,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1598,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,1598,1623]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Female abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with median lobe covering approximately two-thirds of posterior margin, trilobed, median lobe slightly narrower and more produced than lateral lobes, with dark pigment indistinct (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1279,1301]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,205,1232]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[188,1398,193,1258]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Females of Cortona: A – D, Cortona minuta: A, first valvula; B, detail of first valvula apex; C, second valvula; D, third valvula. E – I, abdominal sternite VII: E, C. minuta; F, C. catanachae; G, C. silvai; H, C. otamendiensis; I, C. concordica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376448/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
