</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="366" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1598,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1886,1911]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is readily distinguishable from all others within 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1094,1887,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1001,1094,1887,1910]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Cortona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the aedeagus with a pair of short apical appendages directed apicad, and shaft curved 70° dorsad with a slim apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1362,1922,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
